reviews.review_text: Big Thanks I've been wondering if an entire copy of this show would ever surface, so big thanks to all those involved in splicing and dicing this together.  I've enjoyed listening to the second set for years, but hearing the whole thing places things into better perspective.  As expected, the sound is iffy in places, but that doesn't overshadow the joy of hearing this show in its entirety.  The five stars pertain to the quality of the musicianship and song choices (franklin's, roses, jam>Jackaroe (!!), World to Give (!!!)), not the sound quality.

best shakedown ever without a doubt the funkiest shakedown i have ever heard. very good sandwiched between playin & world to give. get it for the unusual 2nd set. the shakedown is for the ages. so funky it hurts.

stellar show this has long been favorite of mine since it was my first show..i have had a decent board coy of second set but am pleased to see and hear what i don't remember.  the beginning of the second set with jam-drums-jam is without weir.  what the problem was i don't know but he doesn't join in until jackaroe. this venue was an excellent place to see them because it was on the lake downtown and small with great acoustics.  best peggyo ever...i'm sure you'll agree...future dicks pick

do not... with apologies to Jonathan, the first set of this show is a horrible recording. I had to grit my teeth through the whole thing. thank god the second set comes thru with great sound; not only that but a wild one too!!!

Great LL-Supp Nearly as good as 2-17-79, but there is only twenty seconds of jamming post-vocals in Supplication.  

Thanks for putting set one together; not sure yet if it rates higher (I reviewed set two on the other SBD recording).

78 rpm great show but hasn't anyone noticed this copy plays fast??!!! Jerry's god, i mean good but cmon!! his voice wasn't that high since puberty:)\



but a BEAUTIFUL show none the less, try the other sbd for best speed quality
five stars for the show two for recording quality
although some shows dare i say could benifit from the bump in speed this is not one of them

namaste,

and bless all the busy archive.org bees!!!

passenger....ouch I find Donna's catterwallin' (in fact, I think if you look in the dictionary under catterwall, you would find a picture of Donna) particularly irritating on Passenger. Otherwise, a decent effort. Seems to me this period between hot 77 and early 80s as a time in which they are searching for the sound. Everything seems to be going through the motions, with sparks of brilliance.

THE CRITICS COMMENTS REGARDING " PASSENGER " SOUND  SO MUCH WORSE............... I'M SURE YOU WERE REALLY DISMAYED WITH THE PICASSO MOON THAT NIGHT IN THE SKY TOO?  ONE CAN'T HAVE A PERFECT DAY ALL THE TIME..LET IT GO.IT'S ALMOST BEEN 20YRS NOW.....THAT WASN'T BAD "PASSENGER"  YOU WEHRE YOUSGER MORE IMPRESSIONALBLE BACK IN 1978.  OH SORRY NOTHING WITH AGE. ...YOU JUST HEARD IT FROM THESE  FILES.  ALMOST 20YR OLD RECORDING WE ARE SO BLESSED TO BE ABLE TO  PRESERVE AND LISTEN TO.  ......REMEMBER ONE OF THE FIRST THINGS YOU LEARNED......
 "SOMETIMES THE SUN IS BLUE AND THE SKY IS YELLOW"

2nd set opening Jam.... WOW! I don't know what Jerry was doing during setbreak, but all I can say is that his playing during the jam to open the second set COOKS.  If you have not heard this, give it a listen for sure.
shakedown st that was a mighty fine solo from jerry
